description:
**Administrative Coordinator**

Beth El Synagogue Center, New Rochelle, NY

Salary range: $45,000-$55,000, commensurate with experience. Benefits include health insurance, generous paid time off and retirement/403(b).

To apply, please send a cover letter and resume to adminjob@bethelnr.org

**Summary** 

Beth El Synagogue Center is a vibrant, egalitarian community located in Westchester County, just thirty minutes from Manhattan. We thrive on activity. Our energetic members and guests of every age come to Beth El for spirituality, learning, socialization and recreation. Our Youth and Family Department, provides a diverse range of educational opportunities and social programs for kids K-12 and their families in a nourishing, engaging, and positive environment for our learners.

We are looking for an enthusiastic and detail-oriented person to join our team. We are seeking someone to provide administrative support for our Youth and Family Engagement Department and to support general synagogue functioning.

**Our Team Values and You**

Our team fosters a culture of experimentation and reflection, celebrating creativity and embracing new ideas. We share one another’s successes and support one another through disappointments. We take initiative and pitch in to help each other. We are looking for someone who embraces these values and is eager to grow with us as we work to serve our community.

Our ideal candidate possesses strong organizational, time management, and communication skills and the ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously with keen attention to details while in a fast-paced work environment. They enjoy working with others and engaging with children and congregants of all ages, are energetic, flexible, and can laugh when things get stressful. They are comfortable with technology and are familiar with Google Suite.

**Responsibilities for the Youth and Family Engagement Department**

Working under the direction of the Director of the Department, you would:

* Provide support to Department Director and our part-time Religious School teachers;
* Be present on-site during Religious School (Thursdays, 2:30-6:30 and Sundays, 8 am-12:30 pm) to support school operations and foster relationships with children and families;
* Communicate professionally and warmly with parents and staff in-person, over the telephone, and via email;
* Interface professionally and kindly with students in grades K-12;
* Maintain and organize records for events and Religious School, such as class rosters, event registrations, progress reports, etc.;
* Assist teachers with preparing materials for classes;
* Manage and regularly update bulletin boards;
* Maintain a neat and organized office, including supply closets, storage room, and basement, and ordering more supplies as needed to support programs;
* Help supervise arrival and dismissal for each Religious School day;
* Attend occasional family community programming outside of working hours;
* Support Youth and Family Engagement programming, special events, and holidays including ordering supplies, food, completing necessary space requests, ensuring proper set-up, and assisting with marketing efforts.

**Responsibilities for Synagogue-wide Projects**

Under the direction of the Chief Executive Officer, provide administrative support for general synagogue programming, including:

* Work collaboratively on event and program logistics (including major programs like our annual gala and High Holidays);
* Manage a system for processing and acknowledging donations;
* Support the creation and distribution of our printed Bulletin, including collecting articles and liaising with Marketing Director and vendor for collating, printing and mailing:
* Prepare materials for meetings;
* Serve as back-up to the Administrative Assistant to the CEO and Clergy team;
* Conduct research and assist with other special projects as needed.

Job Type: Part-time

Pay: $45,000.00 - $55,000.00 per year

Expected hours: 40 per week

Benefits:

* 401(k)
* 401(k) matching
* Health insurance
* Paid time off

Experience:

* Customer service: 2 years (Preferred)

Ability to Commute:

* New Rochelle, NY 10804 (Required)

Ability to Relocate:

* New Rochelle, NY 10804: Relocate before starting work (Required)

Work Location: In person
